		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />NESticle was my 'first', back in 97. Playing online seemed unreal at the time...
<br />
<br />I also dredged up an <a href="http://cool.conservation-us.org/mirrors/faq/emulators/part3" class="postlink">emulator FAQ</a> from 1997 that mentions four current NES emulators: LandyNES, NESA, PasoFami, and iNES. They seem to be the four earliest.
<br />
<br />Anyone have early versions of these sitting on a hard drive (or at least Landy and NESA, since the others are technically shareware)? A thread from a few years back requested LandyNES, but nothing came of it.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
